FARMERS’ FEED CO., Appellant, v. DAVID STEVENSON BREWING CO., Respondent. (City Court of New York,

General Term.

May 28, 1900.) Action by the Farmers’ Feed Company against the David Stevenson Brewing Co. From a judgment dismissing the complaint, plaintiff appeals. Reversed. Paskusz & Cohen, for appellant. William G. McCr'ea, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

The complaint sets forth a good cause of action. It was error to dismiss it. Judgment reversed. New trial ordered, with costs to appellant.
